DAX Depo Dataset Analysis Project (Power BI)
📌 Project Overview

In this project, I worked with the DAX Depo dataset to analyze business performance using Power BI and DAX functions.

🗂️ Data Model

I used multiple tables such as Sales, Returns, Customers, Products, Dates, and Regions to build a proper data model.

The DAX Depo dataset mainly consists of:

2 Fact Tables: Sales, Returns
4 Dimension Tables: Region, Customers, Date, Products

🧮 Calculated Columns

I created several calculated columns to enhance data usability:

Profit: Calculated by subtracting Cost from Sales Amount in the Sales_Fact table
Return Flag: Added to identify whether a product was returned in the Sales_Fact table
Full Customer Name: Created by combining first and last names in the Customer_Dim table
📈 Measures Created

I developed key measures to analyze business performance:

 -Total Sales
 -Total Cost
 -Total Profit
 -Return Rate (% of returned items)
 -Average Sales per Transaction

⚡ Advanced Analysis (Quick Measures)

I used Quick Measures to perform advanced analysis:

 - Compared sales growth year-over-year (YoY)

🧩 Measure Table

To maintain organization, I created a separate Measure Table for all DAX calculations.

🔍 Filter Context & DAX Functions

I worked with filter context and data behavior using the following functions:

ALL()
FILTER()
CALCULATE()

This helped in comparing sales across regions with and without filters.

